==English==
===Etymology===
Old English adjective ''bærlīc'' from the noun ''[[bere]]''
===Noun===
'''barley''' (''uncountable'')

# A type of [[grass]], ''[[Hordeum vulgare]]'', or the grains of this grass used as food.

